        Constructor for the HotelRoom pojo.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the hotel.
        location - The city that the hotel is located in.
        roomSize - The size of the room.
        isSmoking - Weather the room allows occupants to smoke.
        rate - The cost of the room.
        date - The date that the room will be available from.

      • HotelRoom

        public HotelRoom(java.lang.String... strings)
        Constructor for the HotelRoom pojo.

        Because the output of the Data.readRecord(String) method looks like 

        0. |Palace                                                          |
1. |Smallville                                                      |
2. |2   |
3. |Y|
4. |$150.00 |
5. |2005/07/27|
6. |        |
        for an unbooked room, it must be heavily parsed.
        Parameters:
        strings - An array of strings ordered to follow the output of the Data.readRecord(String) method.
